<dl id="n53083i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53083i">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53083i"> 83(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> confession / tomb of martyr shrine, <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n53083i"><li>FW 341.27 </li><li><a href="../../flex/md/lexmd.htm#n53083i">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/md/l39md.htm#n53083i">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n53083i">MS BL 47480-112</ms> </li><li>JJA 55:201 <a name="mdd6dash" href="../../FF/fdra/mda.htm#mdd6dash">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/md/mdd6.htm#n53083i">Draft: II.3&sect;4.6</a>' </li> </ul><mm class="note">Note: The Latin word <i>confessio</i> was formely applied to the tomb in which the body of a martyr was lain. It came later to denote the shrine in which the relics of a martyr were placed. [In text with shrive (confess), also the parenthesis in the next line may refer, with ossuary (urn for bones of the dead), Latin <i>bonum</i> (good) and notion &lsquo;as sure as there&apos;s a bone in your osteology&rsquo;.] </mm> </dd></dl>
